<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="429" pageId="1" pageNumber="428" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1901,2034]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,151,248]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="429" pageId="1" pageNumber="428">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,577,1937,1962]" pageId="1" pageNumber="428">Diagnosis (macropterous male).</emphasis>
Body large (ca. 
<quantity box="[764,829,1938,1962]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="428" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
long, 
<figureCitation box="[900,964,1937,1962]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1900,1922]" captionTargetBox="[182,1405,334,1846]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,303,1875]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Holotype of Criniverticillus longicumulus Lin, Yao &amp; Ren gen. et sp. nov. CNU-COC-MA2018001. Photomicrographs of (A) dorsal and (B) ventral views; line drawings of (C) dorsal and(D) ventral views.Scale bars = 1.0 mm. afp: anterior flexing patch; dse: dorsal simple eye; en: endophallus; mrt: median ridge on tergite; pfp: posterior flexing patch; sscr: sensorium on subcostal ridge; tp: tubercular projection." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1216664/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="428">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
); antenna long (ca. 
<quantity box="[1190,1327,1938,1962]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="2.4" metricValueMin="2.1" pageId="1" pageNumber="428" unit="mm" value="2.25" valueMax="2.4" valueMin="2.1">2.1â€“2.4 mm</quantity>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1339,1423,1937,1962]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1333,1355]" captionTargetBox="[178,1405,201,1280]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,171,1311]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Detailed photographs of Criniverticillus longicumulus Lin, Yao &amp; Ren gen. et sp. nov. holotype, CNU-COC- MA2018001. (A) dorsal and (B) ventral views of body; (C) left tubercular projection on apex of abdomen in (B); (D) ventral view of right mid- and hind legs; (E) claw, tarsus and part of tibia (note bifurcate setae and spine-likeclaw digitules) in (D); (F) ventral view of antennae; (G) apical antennal segment in (F); (H) lateral view of apex of antenna (note basiconic sensilla); (I) dorsal view offorewing; (J)dorsal view of hamulohalteres.Scale bars for A, B,D, F, I = 0.4 mm; C = 0.05 mm;E, G, H, J = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1216666/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="428">Fig. 2F</figureCitation>
), most antennal setae forming distinct whorls, antennal apical segment with curved bristles (
<figureCitation box="[1165,1256,1973,1998]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1333,1355]" captionTargetBox="[178,1405,201,1280]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,171,1311]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Detailed photographs of Criniverticillus longicumulus Lin, Yao &amp; Ren gen. et sp. nov. holotype, CNU-COC- MA2018001. (A) dorsal and (B) ventral views of body; (C) left tubercular projection on apex of abdomen in (B); (D) ventral view of right mid- and hind legs; (E) claw, tarsus and part of tibia (note bifurcate setae and spine-likeclaw digitules) in (D); (F) ventral view of antennae; (G) apical antennal segment in (F); (H) lateral view of apex of antenna (note basiconic sensilla); (I) dorsal view offorewing; (J)dorsal view of hamulohalteres.Scale bars for A, B,D, F, I = 0.4 mm; C = 0.05 mm;E, G, H, J = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1216666/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="428">Fig. 2G</figureCitation>
); hamulohaltere leaf-shaped; basisternum without a median ridge (
<figureCitation box="[710,797,2009,2034]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1333,1355]" captionTargetBox="[178,1405,201,1280]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,171,1311]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Detailed photographs of Criniverticillus longicumulus Lin, Yao &amp; Ren gen. et sp. nov. holotype, CNU-COC- MA2018001. (A) dorsal and (B) ventral views of body; (C) left tubercular projection on apex of abdomen in (B); (D) ventral view of right mid- and hind legs; (E) claw, tarsus and part of tibia (note bifurcate setae and spine-likeclaw digitules) in (D); (F) ventral view of antennae; (G) apical antennal segment in (F); (H) lateral view of apex of antenna (note basiconic sensilla); (I) dorsal view offorewing; (J)dorsal view of hamulohalteres.Scale bars for A, B,D, F, I = 0.4 mm; C = 0.05 mm;E, G, H, J = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1216666/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="428">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
); abdominal tergites well developed and sclerotized, first three tergites each with distinct median ridge (
<figureCitation box="[675,766,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1333,1355]" captionTargetBox="[178,1405,201,1280]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,171,1311]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Detailed photographs of Criniverticillus longicumulus Lin, Yao &amp; Ren gen. et sp. nov. holotype, CNU-COC- MA2018001. (A) dorsal and (B) ventral views of body; (C) left tubercular projection on apex of abdomen in (B); (D) ventral view of right mid- and hind legs; (E) claw, tarsus and part of tibia (note bifurcate setae and spine-likeclaw digitules) in (D); (F) ventral view of antennae; (G) apical antennal segment in (F); (H) lateral view of apex of antenna (note basiconic sensilla); (I) dorsal view offorewing; (J)dorsal view of hamulohalteres.Scale bars for A, B,D, F, I = 0.4 mm; C = 0.05 mm;E, G, H, J = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1216666/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="429">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
); abdominal tergites VI and VII each with a transverse row of 7â€“9 tubular ducts (
<figureCitation box="[398,489,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1333,1355]" captionTargetBox="[178,1405,201,1280]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,171,1311]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Detailed photographs of Criniverticillus longicumulus Lin, Yao &amp; Ren gen. et sp. nov. holotype, CNU-COC- MA2018001. (A) dorsal and (B) ventral views of body; (C) left tubercular projection on apex of abdomen in (B); (D) ventral view of right mid- and hind legs; (E) claw, tarsus and part of tibia (note bifurcate setae and spine-likeclaw digitules) in (D); (F) ventral view of antennae; (G) apical antennal segment in (F); (H) lateral view of apex of antenna (note basiconic sensilla); (I) dorsal view offorewing; (J)dorsal view of hamulohalteres.Scale bars for A, B,D, F, I = 0.4 mm; C = 0.05 mm;E, G, H, J = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1216666/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="429">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
) extruding wax filaments; a pair of short tubercular projections present on apex of abdominal segment VIII (
<figureCitation box="[440,535,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1333,1355]" captionTargetBox="[178,1405,201,1280]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,171,1311]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Detailed photographs of Criniverticillus longicumulus Lin, Yao &amp; Ren gen. et sp. nov. holotype, CNU-COC- MA2018001. (A) dorsal and (B) ventral views of body; (C) left tubercular projection on apex of abdomen in (B); (D) ventral view of right mid- and hind legs; (E) claw, tarsus and part of tibia (note bifurcate setae and spine-likeclaw digitules) in (D); (F) ventral view of antennae; (G) apical antennal segment in (F); (H) lateral view of apex of antenna (note basiconic sensilla); (I) dorsal view offorewing; (J)dorsal view of hamulohalteres.Scale bars for A, B,D, F, I = 0.4 mm; C = 0.05 mm;E, G, H, J = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1216666/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="429">Fig. 2 C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
